# Spam SMS Detection using Machine Learning

This project classifies text messages as **Spam** or **Ham (Not Spam)** using Natural Language Processing (NLP) and machine learning algorithms. It demonstrates text preprocessing, feature extraction with TF-IDF, model training, and evaluation.

---

## ðŸ“Š Dataset
- **Source:** Kaggle â€“ [SMS Spam Collection Dataset](https://www.kaggle.com/datasets/uciml/sms-spam-collection-dataset)
- **Records:** 5,574 messages  
- **Features:** `message` (text) and `label` (spam / ham)

---

## ðŸ§  Workflow
1. **Text Preprocessing:**  
   - Remove punctuation, stopwords, and convert text to lowercase.  
   - Tokenization and Lemmatization.  
2. **Feature Extraction:**  
   - Transform text into numerical form using **TF-IDF Vectorization**.  
3. **Model Training:**  
   - Train classification models on preprocessed text data.  
4. **Evaluation:**  
   - Evaluate using accuracy, precision, recall, F1-score, and confusion matrix.  
5. **Model Tuning:**  
   - Apply `GridSearchCV` for parameter optimization.

---

## ðŸ§© Models Used
- **Multinomial NaÃ¯ve Bayes:** Ideal for text data and word frequency features.  
- **Logistic Regression:** Strong baseline for binary classification.  
- **Support Vector Machine (SVM):** Effective for high-dimensional text vectors.

*(Multinomial NaÃ¯ve Bayes achieved the best performance on TF-IDF features.)*

---

## ðŸ“ˆ Results
- **Best Model:** Multinomial NaÃ¯ve Bayes  
- **Accuracy:** 0.98  
- **Precision:** 0.97  
- **Recall:** 0.95  
- **F1-Score:** 0.96  

